Adam London signs new one-year Middlesex contract
Middlesex batsman Adam London has signed a new one-year contract.The 24-year-old left-hander scored almost 800 runs for the club's second XI last season at an average of just under 40.Managing director of cricket Angus Fraser said: "Despite a lack of first team opportunities Adam continues to impress the management team."We believe he has the game that will allow him to score runs in first-class cricket when opportunities come along."He added: "Theretirement of Andrew Straussanddeparture of Scott Newmanand Tom Scollay means that Adam is more likely to feature in the first eleven in 2013."London has scored three half-centuries in his nine first-class appearances for Middlesex.